Round 1 [May 7]
Vasco         1-1 Americano
Flamengo      1-1 Botafogo     [May 10]
Fluminense    2-1 Bangu        [May 11]

Round 2 [May 14]
Vasco         2-2 Fluminense
Bangu         0-0 Botafogo
Americano    0-WO Flamengo     [rescheduled to Jul 1; Flamengo did't play; awarded 1-0]

Round 3 [May 18]
Flamengo      0-2 Fluminense
Americano     0-1 Botafogo
Vasco         4-0 Bangu

Round 4 [May 25]
Fluminense    1-1 Americano
Bangu         0-1 Flamengo
Botafogo      0-2 Vasco

Round 5 [Jul 2,3]
Flamengo     WO-0 Vasco        [Jul 3; Flamengo did't play; awarded 1-0]
Fluminense    2-1 Botafogo
Americano     2-1 Bangu        [May 31]

[Due to the postponement of this round, on request of Vasco who
 had 4 players called for international duty, Flamengo has 
 withdrawn from the championship; their remaining two matches
 were awarded 0-1 against them.]

Table:
 
 1.Vasco da Gama   5  3  2  0  10- 3  11
 2.Fluminense      5  3  2  0   9- 5  11
 3.Americano       5  2  2  1   5- 4   8
 4.Botafogo        5  1  2  2   3- 5   5
 5.Flamengo        5  1  1  3   2- 5   4
 6.Bangu           5  0  1  4   2- 9   1

Vasco win third stage and play off for the championship with Botafogo.


Championship Playoff

Botafogo starts with 4 bonus points

First Match [Jul 5]
Vasco         1-0 Botafogo

Second Match [Jul 8]
Botafogo      1-0 Vasco

Table:
 
 1.Botafogo        2  1  0  1   1- 1   7
 2.Vasco da Gama   2  1  0  1   1- 1   3

First team to reach 6 points wins title.

Botafogo Carioca champions 1997.


BOTAFOGO 1 x 0 VASCO
Data – 08 / 07 / 1997
Local – Maracanã (público - 16.854)
Árbitro – Sidrack Marinho
Gol – 1° tempo: 0 a 0; Final: Botafogo 1 a 0, Dimba
Botafogo – Wagner, Wilson Goiano, Jorge Luiz, Gonçalves e Jefferson; Marcelinho Paulista,
Pingo, Djair e Aílton (Marcelo Alves); Bentinho e Dimba (Róbson). Técnico: Joel Santana.
Vasco – Caetano, Pimentel, Moisés, Alex e Felipe; Luisinho, Fabrício, Juninho (Luiz Cláudio)
e Ramon (Brener); Pedrinho e Edmundo. Técnico: Antônio Lopes.


Topscorers:

Romário (Flamengo), 18 gols.
Ramon (Vasco), 14.
Bentinho (Botafogo), 10.
Serginho (Bangu), Sorato (Botafogo) e Edmundo (Vasco), 9.


